DOM events : 
HTML events in JS:
When a user clicks the mouse
When a web page has loaded
When an image has been loaded
When the mouse moves over an element
When an input field is changed
When an HTML form is submitted
When a user strokes a key


i. OnChange Event : Occure when their is a change in the focus of element

ii. The onmouseover and onmouseout Events OnMouseMove etc.


- Dynamically adding elements in HTML :
new element to the HTML DOM, you must create the element (element node) first, and then append it to an existing element.

